product_name: NeutrogenaMakeup Remover Cleansing Towelettes, Fragrance Free Singles
summary: SummaryHighlightsClean IngredientsVeganSustainable PackagingGive BackGently cleanse skin with Neutrogena's Makeup Remover Cleansing Towelettes, Fragrance Free Singles. These makeup remover wipes work to dissolve all traces of dirt, oil & makeup for fresh, clean-looking skin, even while traveling and on-the-go.
details: DetailsBenefitsSoft, pre-moistened Neutrogena Fragrance-Free Makeup Remover Face Wipes Singles gently cleanse skinRemove makeup and effectively cleanse skin in one easy step with these facial cleansing towelettesMakeup remover wet wipes cleanse & remove dirt, oil, makeup, sweat, sunscreen & pollution on skinIndividually wrapped wipes for effective cleansing & makeup removal anywhere with no need to rinseOphthalmologist, dermatologist & hypoallergenic, face wipes are suitable for contact lens wearersDesigned with the earth in mind, the face wipes are made with 100% plant-based clothResearch ResultsRemove up to 99% of makeup even stubborn waterproof mascara with these makeup remover wipesFormulated WithoutFragrancePhthalatesParabensSulfatesAlcoholsSoapsDyesItem 2554008How To UseGently wipe over eyelids, face, lips, and neck. No rinsing required. Dispose of towelette in trash receptacle (do not flush).Precautions: Keep out of reach of children. Do not eat/swallow.IngredientsWater, Decyl Isostearate, Isopropyl Isostearate, Dimethicone, Isohexadecane, Hexylene Glycol, PEG-6 Caprylic/Capric Glycerides, Trisiloxane, Phenoxyethanol, Sucrose Cocoate, Chlorphenesin, Polysorbate 20, Acrylates/C10-30 Alkyl Acrylate Crosspolymer, Sodium Hydroxide.
how_to_use: Gently wipe over eyelids, face, lips, and neck. No rinsing required. Dispose of towelette in trash receptacle (do not flush).Precautions: Keep out of reach of children. Do not eat/swallow.

Gentle and effective. 
Removes all my makeup,including mascara.
I'm a convert,from cleansing balm to these amazing wipes.
One wipe removes all my makeup.
One side for my face,the other for my eyes.
Great product  I highly recommend them!

reviews.headline: Not for acne prone skin.
reviews.comments: I bought this on a whim because i got a free sample in the mail and really liked how made my face feel and i used it before applying my makeup which was a good primer imo. I have acne prone skin and i have eczema. I think this product has been causing all the cystic acne and weird little texture bumps i have been getting all month. It doesn't burn and it actually feels really nice applying to my skin like its taking a sip of water. But i definitely dont think its helping me. Oh well i'll be on a hunt to find a moisturizer that really works for me and my skin.

reviews.headline: Bring back the original WATER GEL
reviews.comments: This new reformulated product is terrible. Bring back the original fragrance free water gel. It was my holy grail. It moisturized well and dried fast, allowed me to do other skin and makeup on top without pilling. It didnt cause acne. It was perfect. This is the exact opposite. Why change something that didnt need touching? Now I have to find a replacement and thats going to be tough finding one like the old version.

faceoff_positive.comments:
Yes. This works sooooo well. I have really sensitive skin and for the past few weeks I have had a dry and sensitive face that feels vulnerable to the elements (wind, humidity, sun and heat damage, stress).

Hydro-Boost did the trick.

I have always liked Neutrogena's products - sunscreen, cleanser, etc. . . .

This one might just be my favorite -

Upon using Hydro-Boost my skin feels hydrated; the water gel is not heavy, it's not oily and it won't make your face look shiny.

You don't need to slather it on even - I just use a little each time and it immediately calms my face -

no redness, no burning - so far soooooo good
faceoff_positive.headline: THIS. WORKS.

faceoff_negative.comments: Please offer fragrance free options for all of your products. Or better yet, just don't add fragrance to anything. Really don't need perfume on my face.
faceoff_negative.headline: Fragrance?
